body.p:
“She charged me,” he adds, “as I valued a mother’s blessing, to watch over him, to set
          good examples for him, and never to forget that he had lost his father”. I religiously confine myself to Mr. G. Bloomfield’s own words;
        and I think I should wrong all the parties concerned, if, in mentioning this pathetic and successful admonition, I were to use any other.

